<span key="59216e3016c9443f9cb855256f5f416e"><span offset-key="59216e3016c9443f9cb855256f5f416e:0">The model in </span>`api/dsService`<span offset-key="59216e3016c9443f9cb855256f5f416e:2"> is an example of using a model to wrap the calls to an internally created API.</span></span>

<span key="00fb873f9a22440f82957ef39b02fa5e"><span offset-key="00fb873f9a22440f82957ef39b02fa5e:0">Example routes of resources</span></span>

<span key="fd062535d7ba42b38b75fd270853dc85"><span offset-key="fd062535d7ba42b38b75fd270853dc85:0">Some examples of routes are provided.</span></span>

# 

<span key="30003689221f4cef80deead65ff993f1"><span offset-key="30003689221f4cef80deead65ff993f1:0">Simple Non-resource route</span></span>

<span key="cb656f8644864e58b69638546514437a"><span offset-key="cb656f8644864e58b69638546514437a:0">The </span>`/`<span offset-key="cb656f8644864e58b69638546514437a:2"> (index) route is a simple </span>`GET`<span offset-key="cb656f8644864e58b69638546514437a:4"> route that is not tied to a resource.</span></span>

# 

<span key="cea09f9edcf7458381e77ade1a51a964"><span offset-key="cea09f9edcf7458381e77ade1a51a964:0">Full CRUD for a single resource</span></span>

<span key="a6fa86b14fda4d0eafeaf2ec6fe1aada"><span offset-key="a6fa86b14fda4d0eafeaf2ec6fe1aada:0">The </span>`/profile`<span offset-key="a6fa86b14fda4d0eafeaf2ec6fe1aada:2"> route is dedicated to a single resource (model).</span></span>

<span key="b4b0806f352e4e0ebbebc0b861c9125f"><span offset-key="b4b0806f352e4e0ebbebc0b861c9125f:0">This route provides CRUD operations on the profile model. Profile is a replacement for the notion of a User when using an identity provider (Okta) where Users are owned by the third party service.</span></span>

# 

<span key="84e32ec7b53a4f098bfd48ed7f28d79a"><span offset-key="84e32ec7b53a4f098bfd48ed7f28d79a:0">Wrapper Routes</span></span>

<span key="fa80ef2b29ee497a96696f63012085ed"><span offset-key="fa80ef2b29ee497a96696f63012085ed:0">The </span>`/data`<span offset-key="fa80ef2b29ee497a96696f63012085ed:2"> routes are wrappers around an internal API (DS resources)</span></span>

<span key="d0e406537e8a4a5c9029a17f61f4b0f4"><span offset-key="d0e406537e8a4a5c9029a17f61f4b0f4:0">When working on a project that has other services being created Labs wants you to keep those behind a single authenticated server. This API starter shows an example of wrapping these services.</span></span>

<span key="b35353e82e9d4b4a98def47ccf2ef726"><span offset-key="b35353e82e9d4b4a98def47ccf2ef726:0">Notice that the </span>`/data/predict`<span offset-key="b35353e82e9d4b4a98def47ccf2ef726:2"> route is not merely a copy of the DS service but creates a path that may be esasier for the FE to consume. Make sure to work with the owner of the service to understand it's use and if such a change will work.</span></span>

# 

<span key="59a30e5a68fb4601ace6e47ce26fc5fc"><span offset-key="59a30e5a68fb4601ace6e47ce26fc5fc:0">Swagger UI Express</span></span>

<span key="aaa2cbc68b2440548622d2b8fd16258f"><span offset-key="aaa2cbc68b2440548622d2b8fd16258f:0">This library is used to setup and serve the offical swager ui resources (html,css,js). The express app is setup to send requests to the route </span>`/api-docs`<span offset-key="aaa2cbc68b2440548622d2b8fd16258f:2"> to the </span>`swagger-ui-express`<span offset-key="aaa2cbc68b2440548622d2b8fd16258f:4"> library.</span></span>

# 

<span key="8c9b4dd53d424f718b66f6dd46123e1c"><span offset-key="8c9b4dd53d424f718b66f6dd46123e1c:0">Swagger JS Doc</span></span>

<span key="67b0df92701141b9ac9b494ea80a4c6b"><span offset-key="67b0df92701141b9ac9b494ea80a4c6b:0">This library is used to parse the root definition file and inline JsDoc comments. The api documentation entries are found inline on the router files in </span>`api/**/*Router.js`<span offset-key="67b0df92701141b9ac9b494ea80a4c6b:2"> and use the yaml notation format. This is the most common format found in swagger reference docs and resources found online.</span></span>

<span key="c2d9c89e3b284ac89d3511293fee0f8a"><span offset-key="c2d9c89e3b284ac89d3511293fee0f8a:0">The </span>`jsdoc.js`<span offset-key="c2d9c89e3b284ac89d3511293fee0f8a:2"> definition file contains the application level information, like app name, version, description and license. You can define reusable components in this file and reference them throughout your jsdoc comments.</span></span>

> <span key="5b38339dffc745079214e8bdaca659a4"><span offset-key="5b38339dffc745079214e8bdaca659a4:0">Take note in the </span>`jsdoc.js`<span offset-key="5b38339dffc745079214e8bdaca659a4:2"> file that tags are used to group routes together.</span></span>

<span key="99ac68aed907491db0841510a588daa8"><span offset-key="99ac68aed907491db0841510a588daa8:0">Testing</span></span>

<span key="de39f2e3b5a54002b2b3eeded678aa26"><span offset-key="de39f2e3b5a54002b2b3eeded678aa26:0">You will be using jest to write function or endpoint/route unit tests in your application. Please put all of your tests for your code in the </span>`__tests__`<span offset-key="de39f2e3b5a54002b2b3eeded678aa26:2"> directory.     <span key="27ecf3b5399b48edbfa4cf9a5c038385">`npm run test`<span offset-key="27ecf3b5399b48edbfa4cf9a5c038385:1"> to run your test suite</span></span>

        <span key="0e372e198a2c4557a3c5e81a1491e57a">*if you're prompted*<span offset-key="0e372e198a2c4557a3c5e81a1491e57a:1"> select </span>`a`<span offset-key="0e372e198a2c4557a3c5e81a1491e57a:3"> to run tests in watch mode.
